<br>
Initially I didn't see the point a council would make other than be yet another forum for arguing however something that Justise said made some sense to me. And this was; &quot;We don't have a very good way of implimenting new ideas...&quot; and I think this is very true.<br>
<br>
I noticed that ever since the one vote was initiated by Vumil, now every little thing we are talking about gets called to be voted on. I think it is making people think that the voting criteria is very arbitrary, and thus the voting process is arbitrary.<br>
<br>
Another good point was that why should level 30 players be voting on issues they have no experience on? Not that I want to exclude anyone's opinions on a subject, but a VOTE should be by those that are going to be affected in the present (at least in my opinion).<br>
<br>
So my idea (Mavrin's really) is that we form a council of prominant raid leaders, and guild leaders (basically active people in those areas that are troublesome; i.e. the higher end spots) to decide on what should be a voted topic and what should remain discussion for now. Say 12-24 people that could meet once a week in chat (and/or have their own message board) to talk about any problems or potential problems in a civilized atmosphere.<br>
<br>
Who and how you want to pick people for this council (if anyone thinks this is a viable alternative to the decision making processes we have now) I will leave up to you guys.<br>
<br>
Remember, the idea for this &quot;council&quot; is just to ratify what the council (through general consensus) thinks is an appropriate topic to be voted on, as opposed to the arbitrary voting we have now. They would also be responsible for setting up the rules for voting (level limits, explanations, etc...) on any particular topic.<br>
<br>
What do you guys think?<br>
<br>
P.S. - and no, I do not wish to be part of this &quot;council&quot; should the idea take off, for various reasons. <p><FONT face="arial" size="-1"><B>Kruunch Spiritslammer (Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim)
