<br>
The second problem of restricting input is simply that you're going to have a hard time getting buy into a system that people aren't represented by.  When guildx gets up to a level that they can/will do things, what exactly is the reason that they should abide by a decision that they had no voice in?  I'm not speaking for/about my guild here, hell I don't think the majority of them want to get to those levels, but I can see what happens in the zones I work in... there are guilds building with pretty obvious intent of becoming planar/raid eligible.<br>
<br>
