<br>
Which is the next point.  Having an uninvolved view provides one advantage.  They aren't voting on what's best for them right now.  Phat lewt, access to a raid, whether that mamber of {Bob's guild} pissed them off isn't as likely to be a factor in their votes/discussions.  Sometimes being distant from a problem helps more than it hurts.<br>
<br>
/shrug, I'm probably going to be flat out ignored or overlooked on this one, but I think you'd be overscrewed by not getting a mixed bag in your council ideea.  You have to involve big guilds, small guilds, and independants, or you're at best creating an uberguild by proxy, at worst creating an impotent beuracracy.<br>
